-- Swiss Re to buy HSBC's UK pensions business
-- 
-- Wed Jun 11, 2014 06:40AM EDT
-- None



ZURICH, June 11 (Reuters) - Swiss Re <SRENH.VX> said on Wednesday it had agreed to buy 400,000 individual and group pension and related annuity policies, as well as 4.2 billion pounds ($7.05 billion) in unit-linked assets from HSBC Life <HSBA.L>.

The deal, made through the reinsurer's Admin Re unit, is expected to be completed in the second half of 2015, subject to regulatory approval, it said. [ID:nASM0006VX]